1
00:00:29,152 --> 00:00:30,912
(Magou Town)

2
00:00:43,759 --> 00:00:45,000
(Meng Guangcai and I)

3
00:00:45,640 --> 00:00:50,460
(reached a major turning point
in our lives in Beiyan.)

4
00:00:51,759 --> 00:00:54,799
(But fate often plays tricks.)

5
00:00:55,759 --> 00:00:59,740
(And those turns can lead
in completely opposite directions.)

6
00:01:03,264 --> 00:01:07,251
(Beiyan County, 1991)

7
00:01:52,760 --> 00:01:53,540
Guangcai.

8
00:01:57,079 --> 00:01:58,040
Zhu!

9
00:02:00,079 --> 00:02:01,040
You're here?

10
00:02:01,439 --> 00:02:02,480
I got transferred here.

11
00:02:02,620 --> 00:02:03,799
Easier for us to catch up.

12
00:02:03,799 --> 00:02:05,359
I just checked in at the station.

13
00:02:05,500 --> 00:02:07,760
That's great. Where are you working?

14
00:02:07,760 --> 00:02:09,219
We'll see you when we have time off.

15
00:02:09,580 --> 00:02:11,080
Much easier to see each other now.

16
00:02:11,300 --> 00:02:12,580
Where are Dazhu and Lijun?

17
00:02:12,860 --> 00:02:13,580
Lijun!

18
00:02:14,580 --> 00:02:15,439
Dazhu!

19
00:02:15,939 --> 00:02:16,819
Look who's here!

20
00:02:17,439 --> 00:02:19,020
Zhu!

21
00:02:19,020 --> 00:02:19,740
Zhu!

22
00:02:19,740 --> 00:02:20,819
- Lijun!
- Zhu!

23
00:02:21,020 --> 00:02:22,599
Zhu, you're here?

24
00:02:22,599 --> 00:02:23,879
Zhu got transferred to Beiyan.

25
00:02:24,379 --> 00:02:25,879
- Promoted?
- Transferred?

26
00:02:25,879 --> 00:02:27,879
It'll be easy to see each other.

27
00:02:28,379 --> 00:02:30,719
Look at you guys, covered in mud.

28
00:02:30,719 --> 00:02:32,819
I will take you guys for a bath.

29
00:02:32,819 --> 00:02:34,080
Great!

30
00:02:34,240 --> 00:02:36,020
But it'll take
a while to finish up here.

31
00:02:36,159 --> 00:02:37,740
Get back to work. I'll wait here.

32
00:02:41,520 --> 00:02:44,020
This is so nice, Zhu. Thanks.

33
00:02:44,379 --> 00:02:46,740
And you treated us to a bath today.

34
00:02:46,860 --> 00:02:49,020
That bathhouse was really nice too.

35
00:02:50,219 --> 00:02:51,520
Eat up. There's more.

36
00:02:52,240 --> 00:02:52,879
Zhu.

37
00:02:53,099 --> 00:02:56,460
Before you brought me
to Beiyan to open my eyes,

38
00:02:56,659 --> 00:03:00,020
I had no idea city construction jobs
were so many, offering food and board.

39
00:03:00,379 --> 00:03:02,360
I can save up and learn a trade.

40
00:03:02,360 --> 00:03:04,080
How's the pay? Is it good?

41
00:03:04,159 --> 00:03:04,879
It's high.

42
00:03:05,500 --> 00:03:08,379
But it's all on credit for now,
haven't been paid yet.

43
00:03:08,379 --> 00:03:09,740
If you need money, tell me.

44
00:03:10,020 --> 00:03:12,379
I was busy with the case
of Zuo Long's disappearance,

45
00:03:12,800 --> 00:03:14,599
having no time to come see you guys.

46
00:03:14,740 --> 00:03:15,319
Zhu.

47
00:03:17,000 --> 00:03:20,240
You've been transferred to the county,
and you're still handling that case?

48
00:03:20,240 --> 00:03:21,520
Without that case,

49
00:03:22,659 --> 00:03:24,599
I should have come
to Beiyan much sooner.

50
00:03:25,860 --> 00:03:27,800
But it's fine. I'm here now anyway.

51
00:03:28,379 --> 00:03:29,879
But the case isn't closed yet.

52
00:03:32,500 --> 00:03:33,580
Did it affect you?

53
00:03:34,000 --> 00:03:35,800
No, don't underestimate me.

54
00:03:35,879 --> 00:03:38,020
It's my duty as a police officer.

55
00:03:38,599 --> 00:03:39,659
But having said that,

56
00:03:39,800 --> 00:03:42,860
I do feel responsible
for Zuo Long's case remaining unsolved.

57
00:03:46,460 --> 00:03:48,379
Saving this egg for the landlady?

58
00:03:48,379 --> 00:03:49,659
If you don't eat it, I will.

59
00:03:49,659 --> 00:03:51,159
I was saving that for myself!

60
00:03:51,159 --> 00:03:52,099
You should eat less.

61
00:04:59,456 --> 00:05:02,176
=The Silent Rift=

62
00:05:02,432 --> 00:05:05,160
=Episode 3=
(Firecracker Man)

63
00:05:08,224 --> 00:05:11,872
(People's police serve the people,
faithful duty ensures safety)

64
00:05:20,660 --> 00:05:22,879
Something feels off.

65
00:05:24,139 --> 00:05:24,879
Got it.

66
00:05:26,100 --> 00:05:27,000
That's better.

67
00:05:27,379 --> 00:05:30,420
T-T-This is way too corny.

68
00:05:30,920 --> 00:05:32,639
Button it up.

69
00:05:32,839 --> 00:05:35,259
Full of righteousness, right?

70
00:05:35,759 --> 00:05:36,819
That's better, isn't it?

71
00:05:37,660 --> 00:05:40,660
No, I think leaving it open a bit...

72
00:05:41,600 --> 00:05:44,199
Isn't this fine?
Naturalism is good, isn't it?

73
00:05:44,980 --> 00:05:46,339
I think leaving it open is better.

74
00:05:46,339 --> 00:05:47,720
It has a manly feel to it.

75
00:05:48,139 --> 00:05:48,759
No buttons?

76
00:05:48,759 --> 00:05:49,420
No, no.

77
00:05:49,420 --> 00:05:50,819
Old-fashioned, buttoning things up.

78
00:05:50,819 --> 00:05:52,660
Wait, bro, straighten up.

79
00:05:53,060 --> 00:05:53,560
Okay.

80
00:05:53,560 --> 00:05:54,980
It's not about buttons.

81
00:05:54,980 --> 00:05:57,160
Look, the shirt is clearly too short.

82
00:05:57,339 --> 00:05:58,160
This is no good.

83
00:05:58,160 --> 00:05:59,100
I have a suit.

84
00:05:59,100 --> 00:06:00,339
You should wear the suit today.

85
00:06:00,339 --> 00:06:01,259
What?

86
00:06:01,699 --> 00:06:02,339
No, no.

87
00:06:02,339 --> 00:06:04,259
You're right. Wearing a suit is correct.

88
00:06:04,259 --> 00:06:05,699
But yours it is useless. Why?

89
00:06:05,699 --> 00:06:07,879
- See how tall he is?
- The suit and this...

90
00:06:07,879 --> 00:06:08,939
See, the same height now.

91
00:06:08,939 --> 00:06:10,040
It's pointless.

92
00:06:10,040 --> 00:06:11,759
Take my clothes. You wear them.

93
00:06:11,759 --> 00:06:12,939
Wait, I have work to do.

94
00:06:12,939 --> 00:06:14,220
Today, I... Forget it.

95
00:06:14,220 --> 00:06:14,819
Don't!

96
00:06:15,819 --> 00:06:16,879
- What?
- Work?

97
00:06:16,879 --> 00:06:17,939
Today is Sunday.

98
00:06:17,980 --> 00:06:19,379
The three of us are here.

99
00:06:19,379 --> 00:06:19,879
Yeah.

100
00:06:19,879 --> 00:06:21,699
So Beiyan can't get by without you?

101
00:06:21,699 --> 00:06:23,480
I'm new here. Still getting my bearings.

102
00:06:23,480 --> 00:06:24,319
I need to go out.

103
00:06:24,319 --> 00:06:26,639
That blind date. Forget it for today.

104
00:06:26,939 --> 00:06:28,759
Bro, bro, take a good look.

105
00:06:28,759 --> 00:06:29,819
She's really pretty.

106
00:06:29,819 --> 00:06:32,139
If you're not going, I think I could go.

107
00:06:32,139 --> 00:06:32,839
Then you go.

108
00:06:32,839 --> 00:06:34,379
Don't mess around.

109
00:06:34,379 --> 00:06:35,720
Listen to me, Zhu Helai.

110
00:06:35,720 --> 00:06:36,759
I have to criticize you.

111
00:06:37,040 --> 00:06:39,759
Personal life is also part
of revolutionary work.

112
00:06:39,759 --> 00:06:41,259
You should thank his wife

113
00:06:41,259 --> 00:06:43,759
for helping solve
your personal problem, right?

114
00:06:44,040 --> 00:06:44,879
Yeah.

115
00:06:44,879 --> 00:06:46,339
I'm telling you one more time.

116
00:06:46,819 --> 00:06:48,540
Don't you take her lightly.

117
00:06:48,540 --> 00:06:49,660
So many people are into her.

118
00:06:49,819 --> 00:06:52,259
She's my wife's colleague
from the linen mill, very nice.

119
00:06:52,879 --> 00:06:54,379
3 PM sharp.

120
00:06:55,100 --> 00:06:56,319
Gate of the Cultural Palace.

121
00:06:56,439 --> 00:06:58,660
Take her to see a movie.
My wife will cover for you.

122
00:06:58,939 --> 00:07:00,379
Zhu Helai, I'm telling you.

123
00:07:00,639 --> 00:07:02,839
Take this to look the part.
I hold this very dear.

124
00:07:02,839 --> 00:07:04,100
- No, I don't...
- Take it.

125
00:07:04,100 --> 00:07:05,439
- No.
- You have to wear it.

126
00:07:05,439 --> 00:07:06,259
Your number, right?

127
00:07:06,259 --> 00:07:07,259
Yeah. I told my wife.

128
00:07:07,259 --> 00:07:09,879
Yes, what number? What if I lose it?

129
00:07:10,759 --> 00:07:12,160
Wait, this hairstyle won't do.

130
00:07:12,319 --> 00:07:13,439
The hairstyle is fine.

131
00:07:13,439 --> 00:07:14,639
Wait, the hairstyle is fine.

132
00:07:14,639 --> 00:07:15,660
- Wait.
- Not fine.

133
00:07:15,660 --> 00:07:16,439
Quick, sit down.

134
00:07:16,439 --> 00:07:17,000
No, no.

135
00:07:17,000 --> 00:07:17,980
Sit down.

136
00:07:17,980 --> 00:07:18,879
Bro, bro.

137
00:07:18,879 --> 00:07:20,139
The hairstyle is fine.

138
00:07:20,139 --> 00:07:21,100
Look at her.

139
00:07:21,100 --> 00:07:21,879
I'm telling you.

140
00:07:21,879 --> 00:07:24,600
Recognize the person
in this photo clearly.

141
00:07:33,439 --> 00:07:34,759
- Pay up!
- Pay up!

142
00:07:36,560 --> 00:07:38,839
- Pay up!
- Pay up!

143
00:07:38,839 --> 00:07:39,660
- Pay up!
- Pay up!

144
00:07:39,879 --> 00:07:42,220
- Give me the money!
- Pay up!

145
00:07:42,819 --> 00:07:44,319
Did I say I wouldn't pay everyone?

146
00:07:44,319 --> 00:07:45,339
Stop it!

147
00:07:45,819 --> 00:07:47,699
Can such a big building run away?

148
00:07:48,040 --> 00:07:48,699
Can it run away?

149
00:07:48,699 --> 00:07:49,639
- But it's...
- Lijun!

150
00:07:50,139 --> 00:07:51,480
Can this big building run away?

151
00:07:51,600 --> 00:07:52,139
Mr. Nian...

152
00:07:52,699 --> 00:07:53,319
Zhu.

153
00:07:53,319 --> 00:07:53,980
What's going on?

154
00:07:54,540 --> 00:07:57,819
Mr. Nian, our contractor,
took away all the steel bars last night.

155
00:07:57,819 --> 00:07:59,199
We think he's going to run away.

156
00:07:59,199 --> 00:08:00,439
Get back to work now!

157
00:08:02,819 --> 00:08:04,879
Everyone has worked hard, right?

158
00:08:04,879 --> 00:08:06,879
Working overtime is all
to meet the deadline.

159
00:08:07,000 --> 00:08:09,160
You hauled away
all these steel bars last night.

160
00:08:09,500 --> 00:08:11,060
T-T-Today, give us a definite answer.

161
00:08:11,259 --> 00:08:12,920
When are you going to pay everyone?

162
00:08:13,060 --> 00:08:14,100
You're the leader, right?

163
00:08:14,480 --> 00:08:16,759
I'm telling you,
disperse the people now.

164
00:08:16,819 --> 00:08:18,540
Delay the topping out, and you're done!

165
00:08:18,540 --> 00:08:19,720
Say that again!

166
00:08:19,720 --> 00:08:20,339
What of it?

167
00:08:20,560 --> 00:08:22,100
Guys, get him!

168
00:08:22,420 --> 00:08:25,259
Don't let him leave!

169
00:08:26,819 --> 00:08:28,540
Police! Police!

170
00:08:32,039 --> 00:08:33,980
Police! Police!

171
00:08:34,480 --> 00:08:35,159
Dazhu.

172
00:08:35,159 --> 00:08:37,659
Don't let him leave!

173
00:08:37,659 --> 00:08:39,600
- Pay up!
- Pay up!

174
00:08:40,000 --> 00:08:40,759
Police!

175
00:08:41,320 --> 00:08:43,840
It's too much, you bully!

176
00:08:44,320 --> 00:08:45,600
- Police!
- Don't let him leave!

177
00:08:47,139 --> 00:08:47,759
Police!

178
00:08:54,200 --> 00:08:55,279
Police!

179
00:08:55,658 --> 00:08:56,320
(Cultural Palace)

180
00:08:56,320 --> 00:08:57,080
Wait for me!

181
00:08:57,460 --> 00:08:58,639
Cream popsicle.

182
00:08:58,940 --> 00:09:00,320
Don't be angry.

183
00:09:00,379 --> 00:09:01,440
How can I not be angry?

184
00:09:01,440 --> 00:09:02,960
It's been ages. He still hasn't come?

185
00:09:02,960 --> 00:09:05,019
Over half an hour waiting.
The sun is baking me.

186
00:09:05,019 --> 00:09:06,519
I just paged him again.

187
00:09:06,519 --> 00:09:07,899
Maybe something came up.

188
00:09:08,580 --> 00:09:10,080
What could be more important?

189
00:09:10,700 --> 00:09:11,840
Cream popsicle.

190
00:09:11,840 --> 00:09:13,080
Lin Shan isn't reliable.

191
00:09:13,080 --> 00:09:14,440
How can the man he got be better?

192
00:09:14,440 --> 00:09:16,200
If you don't trust him,
don't you trust me?

193
00:09:16,200 --> 00:09:17,700
You're his wife. Equally unreliable.

194
00:09:18,960 --> 00:09:19,940
He's really handsome.

195
00:09:19,940 --> 00:09:20,899
Believe me.

196
00:09:20,899 --> 00:09:21,639
Don't worry.

197
00:09:21,639 --> 00:09:22,379
It's skin-deep.

198
00:09:22,379 --> 00:09:24,200
He might be handsome,
but he's unreliable.

199
00:09:24,200 --> 00:09:25,139
Alright, calm down.

200
00:09:25,139 --> 00:09:26,440
I'll page him ten times, okay?

201
00:09:26,440 --> 00:09:28,019
I'll buy you a soda to cool you down.

202
00:09:28,019 --> 00:09:28,899
What a flake.

203
00:09:28,899 --> 00:09:29,639
- Wait.
- Listen.

204
00:09:29,639 --> 00:09:30,960
I'd never, ever date him.

205
00:09:31,639 --> 00:09:33,139
Don't leave. Be good.

206
00:09:36,960 --> 00:09:38,460
The Zuo Long case taught you nothing?

207
00:09:39,340 --> 00:09:41,639
Keep it civil. Talk it out.

208
00:09:46,639 --> 00:09:47,399
Zhu.

209
00:09:48,200 --> 00:09:49,519
You even flashed your badge.

210
00:09:50,460 --> 00:09:52,340
That man still hasn't paid up.

211
00:09:53,399 --> 00:09:55,580
Would anything I say make a difference?

212
00:09:56,200 --> 00:09:57,460
If you hit him,

213
00:09:57,820 --> 00:10:00,139
even if we're in the right,
we'd be in the wrong.

214
00:10:02,139 --> 00:10:03,899
I didn't intend
to get physical with him.

215
00:10:05,580 --> 00:10:09,519
Isn't paying back debts
the universal truth?

216
00:10:13,519 --> 00:10:14,519
Zhu, sit here.

217
00:10:17,580 --> 00:10:20,080
We've been out here so long.

218
00:10:21,019 --> 00:10:22,960
We can't just go back empty-handed.

219
00:10:23,460 --> 00:10:27,019
Asking him for money makes us
look like we're making trouble.

220
00:10:27,879 --> 00:10:30,519
Just because he's acting shamelessly,
are we out of options?

221
00:10:30,519 --> 00:10:31,580
Alright, stop talking.

222
00:10:32,259 --> 00:10:34,940
I'll help mediate this.

223
00:10:40,340 --> 00:10:42,019
Bullied by Zuo Long back in the village,

224
00:10:43,019 --> 00:10:44,580
and out here, by the boss.

225
00:10:45,340 --> 00:10:47,200
If Mr. Nian wants
to get this building built,

226
00:10:47,340 --> 00:10:48,879
he has to uphold his business credit.

227
00:10:48,960 --> 00:10:51,320
If he doesn't keep
his word, we'll sue him.

228
00:10:52,700 --> 00:10:53,779
Does suing him cost money?

229
00:10:56,960 --> 00:10:57,840
Zhu, you seem tied up.

230
00:10:57,840 --> 00:10:59,460
G-Go ahead.

231
00:11:02,840 --> 00:11:04,019
Zhu.

232
00:11:05,340 --> 00:11:06,700
See? Do you believe me now?

233
00:11:06,700 --> 00:11:09,019
I told you, Zhu is Guangcai's friend.

234
00:11:09,019 --> 00:11:11,519
He's a policeman.
He'll definitely help us get justice.

235
00:11:11,519 --> 00:11:12,019
Yeah.

236
00:11:12,019 --> 00:11:13,399
He'll help us get justice.

237
00:11:13,399 --> 00:11:15,639
Dazhu, what nonsense are you spouting?

238
00:11:16,820 --> 00:11:18,580
Say thank you to Zhu.

239
00:11:18,580 --> 00:11:19,519
Thank you.

240
00:11:19,519 --> 00:11:20,700
- Thank you, Zhu.
- Thank you.

241
00:11:21,080 --> 00:11:21,580
Alright.

242
00:11:21,580 --> 00:11:22,200
Shut up.

243
00:11:22,519 --> 00:11:23,639
I've got some things to do.

244
00:11:23,840 --> 00:11:26,460
I'll come back once I'm done.

245
00:11:27,019 --> 00:11:27,960
Don't worry.

246
00:11:28,639 --> 00:11:30,700
- Thank you, Zhu.
- Thank you, Zhu.

247
00:11:32,779 --> 00:11:33,960
Zhu, be careful.

248
00:11:33,960 --> 00:11:34,700
Got it.

249
00:11:38,019 --> 00:11:39,080
You were talking nonsense.

250
00:11:40,080 --> 00:11:42,399
Zhu even showed his badge.

251
00:11:49,379 --> 00:11:51,139
Popsicles! Ice cream!

252
00:11:52,840 --> 00:11:54,399
Popsicles!

253
00:11:55,080 --> 00:11:56,080
Where is she?

254
00:11:56,759 --> 00:11:59,840
She says I'm unreliable?
Who's the unreliable one?

255
00:12:15,080 --> 00:12:15,899
My bag!

256
00:12:15,899 --> 00:12:18,080
Stop the thief!

257
00:12:18,320 --> 00:12:19,519
Catch the thief!

258
00:12:19,519 --> 00:12:20,200
Stop!

259
00:12:24,580 --> 00:12:25,279
(Badge)
Police!

260
00:13:14,840 --> 00:13:15,700
Come on, drink!

261
00:13:15,700 --> 00:13:17,399
Come on, a toast to Mr. Nian!

262
00:13:27,759 --> 00:13:29,639
Mr. Nian, who's this?

263
00:13:31,340 --> 00:13:32,139
Who is it?

264
00:13:42,460 --> 00:13:44,820
Well? Can't get rid of you?

265
00:13:46,139 --> 00:13:46,960
Mr. Nian.

266
00:13:46,960 --> 00:13:50,639
I came to apologize
for what happened earlier today.

267
00:13:50,639 --> 00:13:51,440
What?

268
00:13:53,279 --> 00:13:54,279
Get lost!

269
00:13:55,440 --> 00:13:56,340
Mr. Nian.

270
00:13:56,700 --> 00:13:59,960
No matter what,
you hired us to work on the site.

271
00:14:00,200 --> 00:14:02,399
You should at least
uphold some basic credibility.

272
00:14:02,519 --> 00:14:04,759
Just pay us what you owe everyone.

273
00:14:07,960 --> 00:14:09,460
Who does he think he is?

274
00:14:09,460 --> 00:14:11,259
He wants to talk to me about credit?

275
00:14:11,259 --> 00:14:12,700
Who is he?

276
00:14:13,840 --> 00:14:14,899
Are you worthy?

277
00:14:15,440 --> 00:14:15,960
I...

278
00:14:22,460 --> 00:14:23,200
Mr. Nian.

279
00:14:23,879 --> 00:14:26,279
You can deduct the cost
of these drinks from my wages.

280
00:14:26,519 --> 00:14:28,080
I'll toast you with this.

281
00:14:28,200 --> 00:14:30,019
Please pay us our wages.

282
00:14:30,399 --> 00:14:32,580
I'm begging you on behalf of everyone.

283
00:14:32,820 --> 00:14:34,019
I toast you.

284
00:14:46,639 --> 00:14:50,200
Do you have any idea
how much this bottle costs?

285
00:14:50,779 --> 00:14:53,519
You owe me money now.

286
00:14:53,519 --> 00:14:54,460
Asking me for money?

287
00:14:54,460 --> 00:14:55,960
I'm firing you right now.

288
00:14:55,960 --> 00:14:57,899
Don't think you'll get
a single cent. Get lost!

289
00:14:58,279 --> 00:14:59,340
- Hear that?
- Get going.

290
00:14:59,340 --> 00:15:00,340
Leave.

291
00:15:00,960 --> 00:15:01,700
Mr. Nian.

292
00:15:02,700 --> 00:15:04,899
If you don't make things clear today,

293
00:15:06,340 --> 00:15:07,460
I'm not leaving.

294
00:15:08,659 --> 00:15:11,220
You want me to make
things clear for you?

295
00:15:13,460 --> 00:15:15,879
You really don't know
your place. Get out!

296
00:15:16,399 --> 00:15:19,379
Don't you understand
what I'm saying? You don't get it?

297
00:15:21,200 --> 00:15:22,259
- Get out!
- Get out!

298
00:15:22,259 --> 00:15:23,019
Get out.

299
00:15:23,019 --> 00:15:24,700
Can't you understand what I'm saying?

300
00:15:29,080 --> 00:15:29,879
Get out.

301
00:15:30,879 --> 00:15:31,700
Get out.

302
00:15:32,519 --> 00:15:33,340
Leave.

303
00:15:33,639 --> 00:15:34,659
Leave.

304
00:16:00,080 --> 00:16:03,379
G-G-Guangcai, how did the talk go?

305
00:16:03,379 --> 00:16:05,879
When are they p-p-paying us?

306
00:16:06,500 --> 00:16:07,139
- Guangcai.
- Guangcai.

307
00:16:07,139 --> 00:16:07,960
Forget the pay.

308
00:16:07,960 --> 00:16:09,139
- Dazhu.
- We can't risk more trouble.

309
00:16:09,320 --> 00:16:09,940
Lijun.

310
00:16:11,320 --> 00:16:12,379
I will get back

311
00:16:13,519 --> 00:16:14,700
the money owed to us.

312
00:16:18,379 --> 00:16:19,899
G-G-Guangcai.

313
00:16:26,320 --> 00:16:28,639
What a great day today to celebrate

314
00:16:28,879 --> 00:16:31,600
(Topping-out Ceremony)
the topping out of the Eagle Building.

315
00:16:32,019 --> 00:16:34,500
Thanks to the county's strong support,

316
00:16:34,500 --> 00:16:36,899
this building was completed on time.

317
00:16:37,259 --> 00:16:37,940
Today,

318
00:16:38,100 --> 00:16:38,779
- Where's Guangcai?
- I'm honored

319
00:16:38,779 --> 00:16:41,320
to have some leaders and guests
to perform the ribbon-cutting.

320
00:16:41,320 --> 00:16:41,960
Applause!

321
00:16:41,960 --> 00:16:43,879
- Great!
- Great!

322
00:16:43,879 --> 00:16:44,600
Come on.

323
00:16:47,960 --> 00:16:49,720
Look! Someone's about to jump up there!

324
00:16:51,519 --> 00:16:52,139
You!

325
00:16:52,139 --> 00:16:53,700
- G-G-Guangcai?
- Guangcai!

326
00:16:53,700 --> 00:16:55,159
Guangcai, what are you doing?

327
00:16:55,159 --> 00:16:56,500
Step back!

328
00:16:57,340 --> 00:16:57,960
Guangcai!

329
00:17:00,100 --> 00:17:01,259
It's not worth it!

330
00:17:01,259 --> 00:17:01,779
Nian!

331
00:17:01,779 --> 00:17:02,519
(Topping-out Ceremony)
Guangcai!

332
00:17:02,840 --> 00:17:03,779
Pay up!

333
00:17:04,259 --> 00:17:05,839
Pay me now!

334
00:17:06,000 --> 00:17:07,019
Why did you go up there?

335
00:17:07,019 --> 00:17:08,819
Get down!

336
00:17:08,819 --> 00:17:12,960
Pay back all the money you
owe the workers right now!

337
00:17:13,099 --> 00:17:14,579
Not a single cent less!

338
00:17:14,720 --> 00:17:15,880
No way!

339
00:17:16,220 --> 00:17:17,779
You think you can threaten me?

340
00:17:17,779 --> 00:17:18,720
You want to jump?

341
00:17:18,720 --> 00:17:20,099
Jump. Do it.

342
00:17:21,680 --> 00:17:23,779
G-G-Guangcai, no, no!

343
00:17:27,500 --> 00:17:28,079
Hello?

344
00:17:32,420 --> 00:17:35,819
Eagle Building construction site.
Someone is going to jump, right?

345
00:17:37,920 --> 00:17:40,599
I declare
the ribbon-cutting ceremony ends now.

346
00:17:41,720 --> 00:17:43,200
Dazhu, don't let him leave.

347
00:17:45,180 --> 00:17:45,940
Pay us!

348
00:17:46,460 --> 00:17:48,720
No one leaves! I dare you!

349
00:17:48,720 --> 00:17:49,460
Stop!

350
00:17:49,460 --> 00:17:50,099
Pay us!

351
00:17:50,099 --> 00:17:50,799
Stop it!

352
00:17:51,259 --> 00:17:52,400
- They can't leave!
- Pay us!

353
00:17:52,400 --> 00:17:53,519
No one leaves!

354
00:17:53,519 --> 00:17:54,220
Pay us!

355
00:17:54,940 --> 00:17:55,559
Pay us!

356
00:17:55,559 --> 00:17:56,180
Stop it!

357
00:17:56,759 --> 00:17:58,279
Give us our money!

358
00:17:59,059 --> 00:18:00,140
No one leaves!

359
00:18:00,140 --> 00:18:00,900
- Pay up!
- Pay up!

360
00:18:00,900 --> 00:18:02,420
Hurry, pay us!

361
00:18:02,420 --> 00:18:03,019
Stop it!

362
00:18:03,019 --> 00:18:04,579
Pay up!

363
00:18:05,259 --> 00:18:07,579
If this firecracker hits my neck,

364
00:18:07,940 --> 00:18:10,579
I'll jump. Try me
if you don't believe it.

365
00:18:10,960 --> 00:18:12,180
I don't believe it.

366
00:18:12,180 --> 00:18:13,799
Go ahead. Do it.

367
00:18:14,019 --> 00:18:14,839
Let him do it.

368
00:18:15,660 --> 00:18:16,440
Don't!

369
00:18:16,440 --> 00:18:17,460
Let's talk this out.

370
00:18:17,460 --> 00:18:19,180
Guangcai, don't!

371
00:18:19,180 --> 00:18:19,880
Guangcai!

372
00:18:20,140 --> 00:18:23,039
Guangcai, come down!

373
00:18:23,779 --> 00:18:24,400
Guangcai!

374
00:18:31,299 --> 00:18:31,920
You.

375
00:18:36,759 --> 00:18:37,380
Handle this.

376
00:18:37,559 --> 00:18:38,160
What?

377
00:18:38,299 --> 00:18:39,900
Deal with it fast. Don't let him die.

378
00:18:43,099 --> 00:18:44,680
Pay us! Now!

379
00:18:46,160 --> 00:18:48,380
Pay! You must pay!

380
00:18:55,420 --> 00:18:57,259
Pay! You must pay!

381
00:18:57,259 --> 00:18:58,559
Pay up! Pay up!

382
00:18:59,019 --> 00:19:01,259
Fine, I'll pay you!

383
00:19:02,880 --> 00:19:03,880
I'll give it to you!

384
00:19:09,519 --> 00:19:11,259
- Great!
- Great!

385
00:19:17,600 --> 00:19:20,960
(People's police serve the people,
faithful duty ensures safety)

386
00:19:29,460 --> 00:19:31,500
(Ma Zhongwu)
Bro, spare a cigarette?

387
00:19:32,700 --> 00:19:33,960
I don't have any.

388
00:19:39,420 --> 00:19:40,440
How'd you get in here?

389
00:19:42,579 --> 00:19:43,700
Setting off firecrackers.

390
00:19:45,339 --> 00:19:46,680
Can that get you in?

391
00:19:48,559 --> 00:19:49,839
You play pretty wild?

392
00:19:55,000 --> 00:19:55,960
Ma Zhongwu.

393
00:19:56,259 --> 00:19:56,839
Officer.

394
00:19:57,339 --> 00:19:57,920
Here.

395
00:20:01,079 --> 00:20:03,819
Buddy, I'm Ma Zhongwu. Keep in touch.

396
00:21:07,799 --> 00:21:08,640
Qin.

397
00:21:13,680 --> 00:21:14,180
You...

398
00:21:15,460 --> 00:21:18,599
It's nothing. See, I'm fine.

399
00:21:19,940 --> 00:21:21,960
I was just scaring them.

400
00:21:23,200 --> 00:21:24,799
Come on, wipe your tears.

401
00:21:24,799 --> 00:21:25,720
I'll do it myself.

402
00:21:25,799 --> 00:21:27,019
As if I'd really jump.

403
00:21:28,700 --> 00:21:30,960
What brings you here? You missed us?

404
00:21:32,640 --> 00:21:34,200
I don't want to stay in town anymore.

405
00:21:36,680 --> 00:21:38,420
Okay, no staying.

406
00:21:38,839 --> 00:21:40,819
I don't want to go back
to Shaguai Village.

407
00:21:42,920 --> 00:21:43,839
Guangcai.

408
00:21:45,960 --> 00:21:47,640
I only want to be with you from now on.

409
00:21:52,079 --> 00:21:52,720
Okay.

410
00:21:53,880 --> 00:21:54,720
We won't stay there.

411
00:21:57,200 --> 00:21:59,259
Guangcai!

412
00:21:59,420 --> 00:22:02,460
Everyone's waiting at the door
to thank you. Come on!

413
00:22:02,460 --> 00:22:03,680
Come say hi with me. Let's go.

414
00:22:04,920 --> 00:22:05,819
Guangcai's here!

415
00:22:05,819 --> 00:22:07,559
- Guangcai's here!
- Guangcai's here!

416
00:22:07,759 --> 00:22:08,920
Guangcai, thank you!

417
00:22:08,920 --> 00:22:10,700
Thanks for getting
our wages back for us.

418
00:22:10,700 --> 00:22:13,000
That money was ours all along, right?

419
00:22:13,000 --> 00:22:14,220
He was wrong not to give it.

420
00:22:14,500 --> 00:22:15,700
Guangcai's right.

421
00:22:15,700 --> 00:22:18,640
Guangcai, everyone wants to treat you
to dinner and drinks tonight.

422
00:22:19,079 --> 00:22:19,920
Just save your money.

423
00:22:19,920 --> 00:22:21,000
Who's paying?

424
00:22:21,000 --> 00:22:23,000
We need to settle this. Who's paying?

425
00:22:23,000 --> 00:22:24,500
- Him! He's paying!
- Who's paying?

426
00:22:24,500 --> 00:22:25,059
I'll pay!

427
00:22:25,059 --> 00:22:25,920
He's paying.

428
00:22:25,920 --> 00:22:27,180
Who?

429
00:22:27,180 --> 00:22:27,960
I'll pay!

430
00:22:27,960 --> 00:22:28,839
You pay!

431
00:22:28,839 --> 00:22:29,920
Let him pay.

432
00:22:30,019 --> 00:22:31,039
I don't have any money.

433
00:22:31,039 --> 00:22:32,299
Please do us the honor.

434
00:22:32,299 --> 00:22:33,819
Please do us the honor.

435
00:22:34,140 --> 00:22:34,759
I'll go.

436
00:22:34,759 --> 00:22:36,059
Alright! It's settled!

437
00:22:36,059 --> 00:22:36,599
Very good.

438
00:22:37,689 --> 00:22:40,431
(Beware of moving machinery)

439
00:22:53,180 --> 00:22:54,799
I just got it washed.

440
00:22:55,299 --> 00:22:56,680
What are you spacing out for?

441
00:23:00,299 --> 00:23:03,420
Do you think there is
anything different about Qin this time?

442
00:23:05,000 --> 00:23:05,759
No.

443
00:23:09,440 --> 00:23:11,559
But I feel like she's got
something on her mind.

444
00:23:11,880 --> 00:23:14,099
Isn't everyone happy?

445
00:23:14,319 --> 00:23:16,000
We're all reunited again.

446
00:23:16,000 --> 00:23:18,700
It feels like being back in Shaguai.

447
00:23:22,920 --> 00:23:23,460
Lijun.

448
00:23:23,700 --> 00:23:26,500
Wouldn't it be even better
if Mr. Chen came?

449
00:23:27,759 --> 00:23:29,880
If only we could really
go back to Shaguai Village.

450
00:23:32,000 --> 00:23:33,299
Got time? Come out with me.

451
00:23:33,799 --> 00:23:34,420
What?

452
00:23:36,079 --> 00:23:37,319
Qin is here.

453
00:23:38,059 --> 00:23:40,420
Don't we need to get
some new food and supplies?

454
00:23:41,200 --> 00:23:43,180
Then you have to buy me popsicles.

455
00:23:43,720 --> 00:23:46,079
All you think about
is eating, you big dummy.

456
00:23:47,616 --> 00:23:57,280
(Beiyan Police Station)

457
00:24:03,420 --> 00:24:04,339
What are you here for?

458
00:24:05,680 --> 00:24:08,680
Hello, sir. I-I-I'm here
for Officer Zhu Helai.

459
00:24:09,440 --> 00:24:13,720
Sir, could you please give
him these eggs and dates

460
00:24:14,700 --> 00:24:15,920
- to him?
- Officer Zhu?

461
00:24:15,920 --> 00:24:17,200
He's getting married today.

462
00:24:17,200 --> 00:24:18,319
Let me go get him for you.

463
00:24:18,319 --> 00:24:19,960
No, no. I know he's getting married.

464
00:24:20,339 --> 00:24:22,019
Give these to him for me.

465
00:24:22,380 --> 00:24:43,920
- Kiss!
- Kiss!

466
00:24:54,200 --> 00:24:55,700
Comrades, let me say a few words.

467
00:24:56,319 --> 00:24:58,440
I'm Liu, Zhu Helai's captain.

468
00:24:59,099 --> 00:25:03,000
Today is the joyous wedding day
of Zhu Helai and Huifen.

469
00:25:03,299 --> 00:25:05,299
We wish them a lovely baby soon!

470
00:25:05,299 --> 00:25:07,339
- Good!
- Good!

471
00:25:08,920 --> 00:25:10,140
There are a few things

472
00:25:10,140 --> 00:25:12,079
I need to remind Zhu Helai.

473
00:25:12,079 --> 00:25:12,799
It's not easy

474
00:25:13,559 --> 00:25:15,940
to marry such a beautiful wife.

475
00:25:16,299 --> 00:25:19,140
I hope you will be diligent
and conscientious in your work

476
00:25:19,519 --> 00:25:21,259
and apprehend more criminals!

477
00:25:21,259 --> 00:25:24,380
- Good!
- Good!

478
00:25:26,079 --> 00:25:26,920
Liu Unity!

479
00:25:27,180 --> 00:25:27,759
Master.

480
00:25:28,339 --> 00:25:30,599
One day as captain
and you're talking like a bureaucrat.

481
00:25:30,599 --> 00:25:32,019
I really can't stand it.

482
00:25:32,019 --> 00:25:32,579
Alright.

483
00:25:32,579 --> 00:25:34,640
Can we let the groom say a few words?

484
00:25:34,640 --> 00:25:37,799
How did a bicycle land you a wife?

485
00:25:37,799 --> 00:25:39,319
- Yeah!
- Tell us!

486
00:25:42,700 --> 00:25:43,819
What?

487
00:25:44,140 --> 00:25:47,579
It was me yelling "stop the thief"
that landed me a husband!

488
00:25:51,319 --> 00:25:52,559
Wait, wait!

489
00:25:52,960 --> 00:25:55,180
We introduced you!

490
00:25:55,180 --> 00:25:56,200
You didn't mention us!

491
00:25:56,519 --> 00:25:59,079
Yeah! Don't you want
to acknowledge your matchmakers?

492
00:25:59,640 --> 00:26:01,380
No, no! You are my great matchmaker!

493
00:26:01,380 --> 00:26:02,880
Toast!

494
00:26:04,579 --> 00:26:06,380
- Come on!
- Come on!

495
00:26:06,380 --> 00:26:07,460
Cheers!

496
00:26:07,460 --> 00:26:09,099
- Happy wedding!
- Happy wedding!

497
00:26:09,099 --> 00:26:10,599
Thank you!

498
00:26:10,599 --> 00:26:13,420
- Wishing you a lovely baby soon!
- Wishing you a lovely baby soon!

499
00:26:14,920 --> 00:26:15,900
Eat a lot.

500
00:26:16,180 --> 00:26:17,519
That table!

501
00:26:17,519 --> 00:26:18,920
Come on, let's toast this table!

502
00:26:20,099 --> 00:26:21,059
Come on, Zhu.

503
00:26:21,059 --> 00:26:21,599
Come on, Zhu.

504
00:26:21,599 --> 00:26:22,799
- Happy wedding!
- Happy wedding!

505
00:26:22,799 --> 00:26:25,599
Your buddy Meng dropped off
some local products. Over there.

506
00:26:26,180 --> 00:26:27,079
Where is he?

507
00:26:27,079 --> 00:26:28,640
He's at the door, refusing to come in.

508
00:26:28,640 --> 00:26:29,460
A moment, please.

509
00:26:33,519 --> 00:26:34,319
Guangcai!

510
00:26:43,500 --> 00:26:44,299
Guangcai?

511
00:26:56,032 --> 00:27:01,026
(Half a year later)

512
00:27:01,299 --> 00:27:02,339
Y-Y-You drink!

513
00:27:02,339 --> 00:27:03,420
It's your turn! Drink!

514
00:27:03,420 --> 00:27:04,460
It's your turn to drink.

515
00:27:06,319 --> 00:27:07,099
Come on.

516
00:27:07,099 --> 00:27:08,319
Good buddies!

517
00:27:08,319 --> 00:27:09,640
Four to four!

518
00:27:09,640 --> 00:27:10,940
Six to six!

519
00:27:11,460 --> 00:27:13,500
You're out again! H-H-He...

520
00:27:13,500 --> 00:27:14,839
He drinks!

521
00:27:15,559 --> 00:27:16,339
It's your turn.

522
00:27:18,420 --> 00:27:19,460
Drink!

523
00:27:20,259 --> 00:27:21,960
That's enough, you guys.

524
00:27:21,960 --> 00:27:22,460
Come on.

525
00:27:22,460 --> 00:27:23,420
Enough drinking.

526
00:27:23,420 --> 00:27:26,319
Anyone who hasn't had enough
can come drink with me over there later.

527
00:27:26,319 --> 00:27:27,299
Come on, drink up.

528
00:27:27,519 --> 00:27:29,420
Come on, let's go drink over there.

529
00:27:30,099 --> 00:27:31,279
Let's go to that table.

530
00:27:32,259 --> 00:27:33,400
He took the liquor.

531
00:27:33,400 --> 00:27:34,960
What does it mean?

532
00:27:36,339 --> 00:27:39,000
He can't drink anymore? He has to drink.

533
00:27:39,000 --> 00:27:40,759
He must drink today!

534
00:27:41,279 --> 00:27:44,180
Come on, quick! Drink up!

535
00:27:44,680 --> 00:27:46,059
What does this mean?

536
00:27:47,339 --> 00:27:50,579
Yeah! Drink! Down it!

537
00:28:09,519 --> 00:28:12,059
I can still drink! I didn't have enough.

538
00:28:12,059 --> 00:28:14,339
I-I-I can still drink three bowls.

539
00:28:40,819 --> 00:28:42,920
Look at how pathetic you guys are.

540
00:28:43,099 --> 00:28:44,839
Want a wife? Go find one yourselves.

541
00:28:45,019 --> 00:28:46,420
Go, go find one.

542
00:28:49,420 --> 00:28:50,019
Lijun.

543
00:28:52,220 --> 00:28:53,059
Happy?

544
00:28:54,579 --> 00:28:57,680
Yeah. Really happy for them both.

545
00:28:58,420 --> 00:28:59,460
I'm happy too.

546
00:28:59,579 --> 00:29:02,140
How about this? Let's go
over there for another drink.

547
00:29:02,140 --> 00:29:04,579
Then come back to mess
with them for their wedding night.

548
00:29:12,799 --> 00:29:14,819
L-L-Let's go.

549
00:29:36,460 --> 00:29:38,180
It's a once-in-a-lifetime thing.

550
00:29:40,380 --> 00:29:43,420
A poor guy like me can only
marry you in a place like this.

551
00:29:46,299 --> 00:29:47,579
I'm sorry.

552
00:30:10,460 --> 00:30:13,180
Do you know how long
I've been waiting for this day?

553
00:30:17,380 --> 00:30:19,059
I've been longing to marry you

554
00:30:21,839 --> 00:30:23,319
and have a child with you.

555
00:30:25,299 --> 00:30:27,000
Son or daughter, either is fine.

556
00:30:30,700 --> 00:30:32,079
I swear

557
00:30:33,140 --> 00:30:37,259
I will give you and everyone
around us a good life.

558
00:30:39,640 --> 00:30:40,640
From now on,

559
00:30:42,220 --> 00:30:43,680
I will always be good to you.

560
00:30:45,059 --> 00:30:46,460
Don't worry about anything.

561
00:30:47,220 --> 00:30:48,519
Don't overthink anything.

562
00:30:54,460 --> 00:30:55,200
Guangcai.

563
00:30:55,200 --> 00:30:55,940
Xue Qin.

564
00:30:56,079 --> 00:30:57,140
Guangcai, are you there?

565
00:30:58,299 --> 00:31:00,440
Zhu is here. Zhu!

566
00:31:01,319 --> 00:31:01,920
Xue Qin.

567
00:31:01,920 --> 00:31:02,880
- Afraid you left.
- Zhu.

568
00:31:02,880 --> 00:31:04,680
- Huifen.
- I thought you couldn't make it.

569
00:31:04,839 --> 00:31:06,579
I was out handling a case.
I just came back.

570
00:31:06,579 --> 00:31:07,299
Let me clean this.

571
00:31:07,460 --> 00:31:08,960
Yes! I was so anxious.

572
00:31:08,960 --> 00:31:10,819
We came straight over,
but we still missed it.

573
00:31:10,819 --> 00:31:11,940
I scolded him the whole way.

574
00:31:12,420 --> 00:31:13,559
- Look how messy it is. See?
- Seriously.

575
00:31:13,559 --> 00:31:14,180
Let me do this.

576
00:31:14,180 --> 00:31:14,880
- No.
- It's fine.

577
00:31:14,880 --> 00:31:15,920
No matter how messy it is,

578
00:31:15,920 --> 00:31:17,460
I must come to your wedding.

579
00:31:17,460 --> 00:31:18,700
I'm not like you.

580
00:31:18,700 --> 00:31:20,759
Dropping off the gift
and running off immediately.

581
00:31:20,759 --> 00:31:21,759
- Wait.
- Exactly!

582
00:31:21,759 --> 00:31:23,839
You had so many colleagues
celebrating with you.

583
00:31:23,839 --> 00:31:26,079
Look at me, just a construction worker.

584
00:31:26,079 --> 00:31:26,940
I was out of place.

585
00:31:26,940 --> 00:31:29,319
No matter what you do,
you're always my dear brother.

586
00:31:29,319 --> 00:31:30,420
Here, pour it.

587
00:31:30,420 --> 00:31:30,940
Come on.

588
00:31:30,940 --> 00:31:32,559
This is a toast to you.

589
00:31:32,680 --> 00:31:34,059
And also a punishment.

590
00:31:34,059 --> 00:31:35,059
I'll gladly take it.

591
00:31:35,339 --> 00:31:36,460
Here, Xue Qin, look.

592
00:31:37,019 --> 00:31:37,579
Huifen.

593
00:31:37,579 --> 00:31:38,960
I stewed a big hen for you.

594
00:31:38,960 --> 00:31:39,940
Thank you.

595
00:31:39,940 --> 00:31:40,960
You two drink too.

596
00:31:40,960 --> 00:31:41,640
Drink.

597
00:31:41,640 --> 00:31:43,180
Let's have a drink together.

598
00:31:43,180 --> 00:31:45,420
Come on. Let me say a few words.

599
00:31:45,420 --> 00:31:48,680
- Alright.
- May we always be harmonious and happy

600
00:31:49,019 --> 00:31:50,700
and love each other like one family.

601
00:31:51,140 --> 00:31:51,700
One family.

602
00:31:51,700 --> 00:31:52,380
- Family.
- Cheers.

603
00:31:52,380 --> 00:31:53,680
- Okay, one family.
- One family.

604
00:31:53,680 --> 00:31:54,920
Cheers, family.

605
00:31:54,920 --> 00:31:55,599
Thank you.

606
00:32:21,079 --> 00:32:23,319
Old man! Duck? Come here.

607
00:32:23,920 --> 00:32:26,319
Seriously? You can't even
handle one old man?

608
00:32:26,319 --> 00:32:27,960
How dare you ask me for money?

609
00:32:29,200 --> 00:32:29,940
Mr. Wang.

610
00:32:30,099 --> 00:32:32,920
Our guys really didn't expect
that old cop to be so tough.

611
00:32:33,339 --> 00:32:34,920
Right now, the cops have two locked up.

612
00:32:35,299 --> 00:32:36,599
And two are in the hospital.

613
00:32:37,180 --> 00:32:38,700
The police keep questioning them.

614
00:32:39,180 --> 00:32:40,200
I really need some money

615
00:32:40,200 --> 00:32:41,700
to settle things with my buddies.

616
00:32:44,720 --> 00:32:49,000
Back when you followed me around,
you were all tough fighters.

617
00:32:49,640 --> 00:32:52,299
What happened?
How did you all become useless?

618
00:32:52,700 --> 00:32:54,339
I'm telling you.

619
00:32:54,960 --> 00:32:58,000
If the cops connect this to me,

620
00:32:58,259 --> 00:33:00,440
I'll beat the crap out of you!

621
00:33:04,920 --> 00:33:06,799
Get out! Get out of here!

622
00:33:33,420 --> 00:33:34,039
Qin.

623
00:33:35,039 --> 00:33:36,079
What are you doing here?

624
00:33:38,779 --> 00:33:39,579
Come in.

625
00:33:45,579 --> 00:33:47,680
I've been watched
ever since I was in Gubei.

626
00:33:47,680 --> 00:33:49,299
I had to dress like this to come.

627
00:33:50,259 --> 00:33:51,559
But only for today.

628
00:33:51,559 --> 00:33:52,779
Tomorrow, it won't matter.

629
00:33:55,420 --> 00:33:56,539
I did what you said.

630
00:33:57,339 --> 00:33:58,500
I went to see Zhu Helai.

631
00:34:01,420 --> 00:34:02,680
Guangcai was arrested.

632
00:34:03,539 --> 00:34:04,839
You should show some reaction.

633
00:34:05,680 --> 00:34:08,519
Just showing your face
in front of him achieved our goal.

634
00:34:09,300 --> 00:34:10,539
He's tight-lipped.

635
00:34:11,519 --> 00:34:12,699
Nothing gets out.

636
00:34:13,059 --> 00:34:14,280
I expected as much.

637
00:34:16,199 --> 00:34:18,300
Since Guangcai managed
to get a signal out,

638
00:34:19,159 --> 00:34:21,500
it means the police
already have some evidence.

639
00:34:21,820 --> 00:34:23,539
He probably won't be back anytime soon.

640
00:34:26,400 --> 00:34:28,400
If the police really have evidence,

641
00:34:30,219 --> 00:34:31,539
could it implicate you?

642
00:34:33,519 --> 00:34:36,440
If the evidence they have involves us,

643
00:34:37,099 --> 00:34:39,780
it wouldn't just be Guangcai taken away.

644
00:34:40,960 --> 00:34:42,460
I came back to tell you this.

645
00:34:43,059 --> 00:34:44,179
Lie low for now.

646
00:34:45,079 --> 00:34:45,960
What I can do

647
00:34:46,219 --> 00:34:48,860
is try my best to manage
the group's affairs for Guangcai.

648
00:34:49,099 --> 00:34:49,699
You.

649
00:34:51,119 --> 00:34:52,619
Be ready to leave at any moment.

650
00:34:53,820 --> 00:34:56,780
So you want to stay behind
to cover for Guangcai?

651
00:35:00,099 --> 00:35:01,119
Starting tomorrow,

652
00:35:01,460 --> 00:35:04,019
I'll show up normally
in front of everyone at the group

653
00:35:04,280 --> 00:35:05,500
to divert their attention.

654
00:35:06,519 --> 00:35:10,039
And try to find out as much as possible
about what evidence they have.

655
00:35:12,619 --> 00:35:14,440
This day came too suddenly.

656
00:35:17,219 --> 00:35:17,840
Qin.

657
00:35:19,179 --> 00:35:20,599
We're prepared.

658
00:35:21,699 --> 00:35:23,039
What's meant to come will come.

659
00:35:26,300 --> 00:35:27,280
How's Xiaoliang?

660
00:35:28,019 --> 00:35:29,679
He spoke out of turn yesterday.

661
00:35:30,320 --> 00:35:31,539
I hit him.

662
00:35:32,300 --> 00:35:34,940
He's been holed up in his room
ever since, refusing to come out

663
00:35:35,699 --> 00:35:36,900
or talk to me.

664
00:35:41,059 --> 00:35:42,039
That little guy

665
00:35:43,559 --> 00:35:44,760
has been weak since childhood.

666
00:35:45,059 --> 00:35:46,280
He's never been through much.

667
00:35:46,800 --> 00:35:49,000
Guangcai's trouble this time
must have hit him hard.

668
00:35:51,619 --> 00:35:55,039
(Meng Xiaoliang, son of Meng Guangcai)
You and Xiaoliang worry me most now.

669
00:36:04,340 --> 00:36:05,260
Don't worry.

670
00:36:06,039 --> 00:36:07,539
Guangcai will be back soon.

671
00:36:12,059 --> 00:36:14,800
According to our days
of watching Caisheng Group,

672
00:36:15,199 --> 00:36:19,000
Jiao Lijun suddenly showed up
in public in Beiyan this morning

673
00:36:19,159 --> 00:36:20,280
and appeared at the company.

674
00:36:20,559 --> 00:36:22,099
Nothing unusual about his movements.

675
00:36:22,099 --> 00:36:23,920
He just met
with a few partner organizations,

676
00:36:24,039 --> 00:36:27,159
saying that he still hasn't given up

677
00:36:27,159 --> 00:36:28,280
on Caisheng Group's IPO.

678
00:36:28,619 --> 00:36:31,920
Still actively cooperating with
the sponsor's internal due diligence.

679
00:36:33,179 --> 00:36:36,659
Jiao Lijun seems very confident
that Meng Guangcai will be out soon.

680
00:36:36,659 --> 00:36:39,699
It seems they don't know
that we have evidence

681
00:36:40,019 --> 00:36:40,940
against Meng Guangcai.

682
00:36:43,059 --> 00:36:44,199
What's your take, Mr. Zhu?

683
00:36:45,340 --> 00:36:47,760
He lay low right after Meng Guangcai

684
00:36:48,599 --> 00:36:49,760
was arrested.

685
00:36:49,960 --> 00:36:51,920
Now, he's coming out all guns blazing

686
00:36:52,400 --> 00:36:53,659
and making such a big show.

687
00:36:54,019 --> 00:36:55,679
Seems like he's confident,

688
00:36:56,300 --> 00:36:58,860
but actually, he's just
putting on an act for us.

689
00:36:59,679 --> 00:37:00,599
I agree.

690
00:37:00,599 --> 00:37:05,340
Neither he nor Wang Dazhu is
on Meng Guangcai's suspect list,

691
00:37:05,800 --> 00:37:08,619
but these three were
very close back in the day.

692
00:37:08,619 --> 00:37:10,360
At the very least,
they know what happened.

693
00:37:11,079 --> 00:37:12,440
Most of our team are tracking

694
00:37:12,440 --> 00:37:18,119
Zuo Long and Ma Zhongwu
based on what Meng Guangcai gave us.

695
00:37:18,559 --> 00:37:20,420
According to
Officer Zhu's report last night,

696
00:37:20,420 --> 00:37:22,820
Wang Dazhu is also in Beiyan City now.

697
00:37:22,820 --> 00:37:25,119
But we haven't pinpointed
his location yet.

698
00:37:25,599 --> 00:37:27,699
Wang Dazhu isn't like Jiao Lijun.

699
00:37:28,460 --> 00:37:30,300
I bet he's about to crack.

700
00:37:31,280 --> 00:37:32,940
I know where he might go.

701
00:37:34,624 --> 00:37:36,672
(Rongfa Noodle Shop)

702
00:37:55,136 --> 00:37:56,992
(Lijun)

703
00:38:05,536 --> 00:38:07,837
(Lijun)

704
00:38:12,039 --> 00:38:12,579
Mr. Chen.

705
00:38:12,699 --> 00:38:13,219
Okay.

706
00:38:15,780 --> 00:38:16,900
It's good.

707
00:38:17,300 --> 00:38:18,420
Take your time eating.

708
00:38:18,420 --> 00:38:20,539
No rush. There's more.

709
00:38:23,719 --> 00:38:25,219
You silly.

710
00:38:25,579 --> 00:38:28,119
You came so early.
My restaurant isn't even open yet.

711
00:38:30,860 --> 00:38:34,559
I'm going on a long trip soon.

712
00:38:35,059 --> 00:38:37,940
I might be gone for q-q-quite a while.

713
00:38:38,460 --> 00:38:42,179
I just wanted to eat
my f-f-fill of these noodles.

714
00:38:46,300 --> 00:38:47,940
Where's Guangcai?

715
00:38:49,360 --> 00:38:50,039
Mr. Chen.

716
00:38:50,900 --> 00:38:53,900
You said there was more, right? Noodles?

717
00:38:54,079 --> 00:38:54,699
Yes.

718
00:38:54,699 --> 00:38:55,800
I'd like another bowl.

719
00:38:55,800 --> 00:38:56,300
Okay.

720
00:38:56,300 --> 00:38:57,900
I'll eat my fill today.

721
00:38:58,420 --> 00:38:59,119
Alright.

722
00:39:32,699 --> 00:39:35,119
Dazhu, no rush.

723
00:39:35,119 --> 00:39:37,280
I'll cut you some more fatty meat.

724
00:39:40,960 --> 00:39:41,780
Okay.

725
00:39:42,800 --> 00:39:43,900
Thank you, Mr. Chen.

726
00:39:45,760 --> 00:39:49,632
(Rongfa Noodle Shop)

727
00:40:06,619 --> 00:40:07,280
Hello?

728
00:40:07,619 --> 00:40:10,019
Zhu, Wang Dazhu
just came out of the noodle shop.

729
00:40:10,440 --> 00:40:11,199
I'll be there.

730
00:40:11,199 --> 00:40:13,059
Zhou, come with me.

731
00:40:13,059 --> 00:40:13,679
Yes.

732
00:40:52,400 --> 00:40:53,059
Lijun.

733
00:40:53,059 --> 00:40:53,960
Where did you go?

734
00:40:55,019 --> 00:40:56,800
I told you to show
your face at the company.

735
00:40:57,960 --> 00:41:00,099
Why didn't you answer my calls?

736
00:41:02,219 --> 00:41:04,300
I went to see Mr. Chen.

737
00:41:04,679 --> 00:41:06,780
I thought if I told you,
you wouldn't let me come.

738
00:41:09,599 --> 00:41:10,820
Did Mr. Chen ask too much?

739
00:41:11,260 --> 00:41:11,840
No.

740
00:41:12,159 --> 00:41:13,320
Come back to the company.

741
00:41:13,320 --> 00:41:14,099
Lijun.

742
00:41:17,159 --> 00:41:20,960
I think Zhu Helai saw me.

743
00:41:21,539 --> 00:41:22,579
I have to leave now.

744
00:41:23,599 --> 00:41:26,260
What do you mean by "he saw you"?

745
00:41:29,860 --> 00:41:32,679
I had some men deal with him.

746
00:41:33,199 --> 00:41:34,800
He probably guessed it.

747
00:41:39,619 --> 00:41:40,219
I...

748
00:41:44,544 --> 00:41:48,480
(Huanxing East Road)

749
00:41:51,860 --> 00:41:52,860
I told you!

750
00:41:52,860 --> 00:41:54,400
Don't act recklessly!

751
00:41:55,039 --> 00:41:56,920
They wanted a reason,
and you gave it to them!

752
00:41:57,460 --> 00:41:58,360
So what?

753
00:41:58,360 --> 00:42:01,199
If you had listened to me,
we would have been abroad.

754
00:42:01,780 --> 00:42:03,679
I just couldn't let this go.

755
00:42:03,679 --> 00:42:06,360
Wouldn't it have been better
if we had left the country?

756
00:42:12,219 --> 00:42:13,300
You can't stay here.

757
00:42:14,360 --> 00:42:16,559
Drive out of Beiyan now. Head south.

758
00:42:16,860 --> 00:42:19,320
If you get stopped,
say you're going on a business trip.

759
00:42:22,099 --> 00:42:24,619
Follow the plan
we discussed, understand?

760
00:42:27,179 --> 00:42:28,039
Got it.

761
00:42:33,619 --> 00:42:34,280
Dazhu.

762
00:42:35,699 --> 00:42:37,360
We are all in the same boat.

763
00:42:37,900 --> 00:42:40,840
No matter what happens,
we stick together.

764
00:42:41,599 --> 00:42:43,119
Remember what we said.

765
00:42:48,519 --> 00:42:49,199
Go.

766
00:42:51,119 --> 00:42:52,199
Get going.

767
00:43:32,576 --> 00:43:33,440
(Dazhu)

768
00:43:42,820 --> 00:43:43,420
Officer Zhu.

769
00:43:52,780 --> 00:43:53,500
Open up!

770
00:44:01,780 --> 00:44:03,300
Wang Dazhu, get out.

771
00:44:05,888 --> 00:44:08,301
(Lijun)

772
00:44:23,599 --> 00:44:24,380
Stop the car!

773
00:44:26,699 --> 00:44:27,460
Wang Dazhu!

774
00:44:34,039 --> 00:44:35,199
I said stop the car!

775
00:44:55,599 --> 00:44:56,860
Get out of the way!

776
00:45:00,960 --> 00:45:02,059
Watch out for people!

777
00:45:02,059 --> 00:45:03,900
Let's all die. Let's all die.

778
00:45:08,500 --> 00:45:09,679
Let's all die!

779
00:45:18,360 --> 00:45:19,320
Can you drive or not?

780
00:45:36,019 --> 00:45:36,840
The car broke down.

781
00:45:36,840 --> 00:45:38,019
So scary.

782
00:45:42,336 --> 00:45:44,339
(Crack down on crime.
Protect the people.)

783
00:45:46,560 --> 00:45:49,495
(Interview Record)

784
00:45:51,019 --> 00:45:51,619
Zhu.

785
00:45:53,960 --> 00:45:56,199
I've already told you everything I know.

786
00:45:57,960 --> 00:45:59,300
What else do you want?

787
00:46:00,840 --> 00:46:03,780
Your buddy Wang Dazhu
had a car accident.

788
00:46:04,599 --> 00:46:05,880
We saved him.

789
00:46:06,800 --> 00:46:08,360
Regarding what you confessed,

790
00:46:09,440 --> 00:46:12,760
we'll have a good chat with him.

791
00:46:17,800 --> 00:46:18,619
Officer Zhu.

792
00:46:19,519 --> 00:46:21,880
Come at me all you want.

793
00:46:22,260 --> 00:46:23,719
Don't involve my buddies.

794
00:46:25,639 --> 00:46:27,119
Look at your attitude now.

795
00:46:28,780 --> 00:46:31,300
Now, you're nothing like
the chairman of Caisheng Group.

796
00:46:31,800 --> 00:46:36,079
More like the labor contractor
I knew back then.

797
00:46:36,940 --> 00:46:38,179
You buddy got involved.

798
00:46:39,360 --> 00:46:40,840
And you're still wasting time?

799
00:46:49,440 --> 00:46:52,920
Your dangerous driving
caused a serious traffic accident.

800
00:46:53,099 --> 00:46:54,719
You ran pretty fast when you saw us.

801
00:46:59,019 --> 00:47:01,880
Wang Dazhu,
I don't have time to waste on you.

802
00:47:02,039 --> 00:47:05,699
Tell me, were you involved
in the 6.10 case in 1993?

803
00:47:07,039 --> 00:47:08,260
It hurts.

804
00:47:14,199 --> 00:47:18,360
Guangcai, your smokescreen might
fool others, but it doesn't fool me.

805
00:47:19,159 --> 00:47:21,360
You threw Zuo Long
and Ma Zhongwu under the bus.

806
00:47:22,619 --> 00:47:23,820
But I firmly believe

807
00:47:25,019 --> 00:47:29,760
Jiao Lijun and Wang Dazhu
are connected to the 6.10 case.

808
00:47:45,260 --> 00:47:46,000
Officer Zhu.

809
00:47:48,559 --> 00:47:50,599
Do you know how hard
business is these days?

810
00:47:53,099 --> 00:47:55,119
Do you know how many obstacles
I've had to overcome

811
00:47:57,039 --> 00:47:58,119
to get where I am today?

812
00:47:59,280 --> 00:48:00,199
Are you aware of that?

813
00:48:03,519 --> 00:48:05,659
You can stare at me
all you want. That's fine.

814
00:48:06,659 --> 00:48:08,119
But do you know how much impact

815
00:48:09,300 --> 00:48:11,539
what you're doing has on Caisheng Group

816
00:48:12,340 --> 00:48:15,260
and how many people will be affected
if you wrongfully accuse me?

817
00:48:15,260 --> 00:48:16,219
Meng Guangcai!

818
00:48:17,599 --> 00:48:18,619
I won't wrong you.

819
00:48:19,519 --> 00:48:20,960
I know you've made your fortune.

820
00:48:20,960 --> 00:48:21,840
No need to tell me.

821
00:48:28,039 --> 00:48:29,440
You know I'm wealthy.

822
00:48:30,699 --> 00:48:31,659
But do you know

823
00:48:32,780 --> 00:48:34,380
how many jobs I've provided for Beiyan?

824
00:48:35,099 --> 00:48:38,420
Do you know how much I've given
to education funds for the poor?

825
00:48:39,860 --> 00:48:42,039
I walked out of Shaguai Village
to get here today.

826
00:48:42,460 --> 00:48:44,019
I want everyone to know

827
00:48:44,019 --> 00:48:47,039
that I, Meng Guangcai,
am a useful member of society.

828
00:48:47,760 --> 00:48:51,039
But you, Officer Zhu,
you don't care about any of this.

829
00:48:51,659 --> 00:48:52,679
What do you care about?

830
00:48:53,539 --> 00:48:56,300
What's your intention
in hounding me relentlessly?

831
00:48:58,960 --> 00:49:00,300
It's personal, isn't it?

832
00:49:03,519 --> 00:49:04,860
For that one...

833
00:49:05,860 --> 00:49:07,039
your buddy from Squad Nine.

834
00:49:07,460 --> 00:49:10,199
That Officer Lin, the one
who got shot in the robbery, right?

835
00:49:14,179 --> 00:49:15,420
But don't forget.

836
00:49:15,760 --> 00:49:16,960
It's because of you

837
00:49:18,059 --> 00:49:19,519
that Officer Lin ended up bedridden.

838
00:49:28,119 --> 00:49:31,460
You turned your buddy
into a permanent vegetable.

839
00:49:32,960 --> 00:49:33,699
Yes.

840
00:49:34,340 --> 00:49:37,599
You want to ease your conscience.

841
00:49:37,840 --> 00:49:40,679
So you've been obsessively pursuing
this case for years.

842
00:49:40,679 --> 00:49:42,519
Even going so far as to wrong me.

843
00:49:42,519 --> 00:49:44,760
Just to find some peace of mind.

844
00:49:44,760 --> 00:49:46,940
To grasp at straws.

845
00:49:49,840 --> 00:49:51,099
I'm really worried about you.

846
00:49:52,300 --> 00:49:53,119
Zhu.

847
00:49:58,360 --> 00:50:00,760
If it makes you feel better, Zhu,

848
00:50:01,500 --> 00:50:03,559
I don't mind staying
here for a few days.

849
00:50:05,260 --> 00:50:06,860
But in the end,

850
00:50:07,960 --> 00:50:10,119
I'll still walk out of here.

851
00:50:10,800 --> 00:50:13,619
By then, your straws will be gone.

852
00:50:17,880 --> 00:50:19,820
How will you live then, Zhu?

853
00:50:54,860 --> 00:50:55,539
Officer Zhu.

854
00:50:56,519 --> 00:50:57,380
What's wrong?

855
00:50:59,280 --> 00:50:59,840
Are you okay?

856
00:51:02,119 --> 00:51:02,880
Officer Zhu.

857
00:51:03,800 --> 00:51:05,300
Can you hear me?

858
00:51:05,619 --> 00:51:06,320
Officer Zhu.

859
00:51:06,940 --> 00:51:07,820
- Officer Zhu.
- Officer Zhu.

860
00:51:12,500 --> 00:51:17,524
=The Silent Rift=
